&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical Secretarial Assistant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Band 2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rheumatology - Clinic Nurse Specialist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lincoln&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;18.75 hours per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual to work at Lincoln County Hospital within the Rheumatology Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The medical secretarial team provides a comprehensive service to the Consultants Clinical Nurse Specialists and their teams and is essential in the provision of a high quality patient experience. The post-holder will support the administration and secretarial teams with their day-to-day duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be an enthusiastic team player and an experienced typist, and will be required to have GCSE English grade C or equivalent as well as typing and word processing skills to RSA level 2, including audio typing experience. A flexible approach to work is required and an ability to get on with others in a team based environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah FletcherJob titleSupport ManagerEmail addresssarah.fletcher@ulh.nhs.ukTelephone number01205 446181&lt;/p&gt;
